=== 体育 ===
[[File:Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-L0827-207,_München,_XX._Olympiade,_Eröffnungsfeier,_DDR-Mannschaft.jpg|250px]]的东德代表队]]
东德在自行车、举重、游泳、体操、田径、拳击、滑冰和冬季运动等项目具有领先地位，这主要归功于20世纪60年代中后期开始[[曼弗雷德·霍普纳|曼弗雷德·霍普纳]]医生的领导。

东德体育成功的一个原因是[[兴奋剂|兴奋剂]]的使用，特别是合成代谢类固醇，这是一种在国际奥委会实验室检测出最多的兴奋剂。<ref>Hartgens and Kuipers (2004), p. 515</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |title=Anabolic steroids in sport: biochemical, clinical and analytical perspectives |journal=Annals of Clinical Biochemistry |volume=40 |issue=Pt 4 |pages=321–56 |pmid=12880534 |doi=10.1258/000456303766476977 |url=http://acb.rsmjournals.com/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=12880534 |author1=Kicman AT |author2=Gower DB |date=July 2003 |access-date=2012-06-19 |archive-date=2012-06-29 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120629013117/http://acb.rsmjournals.com/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=12880534 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>东德实施了部分国家主导的兴奋剂计划以帮助提高竞技成绩，使这个人口较少的国家成为在20世纪七八十年代获得了大量奥运会和世锦赛金牌。<ref>Tagliabue, John. – [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0CE7D81039F931A25751C0A967958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=2 "Political Pressure Dismantles East German Sports Machine"] – ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'' – 12 February 1991 | Janofsky, Michael. – [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&res=9D0CE1DA1731F930A35751C1A967958260 "OLYMPICS; Coaches Concede That Steroids Fueled East Germany's Success in Swimming"] {{Wayback|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&res=9D0CE1DA1731F930A35751C1A967958260|date=20100918213312}} – ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'' – 3 December 1991 | Kirschbaum, Erik. – [http://www.rediff.com/sports/2000/sep/15germ.htm "East German dope still leaves tracks"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rediff.com/sports/2000/sep/15germ.htm|date=20080603040130}} – Rediff from [[Reuters|Reuters]] – 15 September 2000 | Ungerleider, Steven (2001). ''Faust's Gold: Inside The East German Doping Machine''. Thomas Dunne Books ISBN 978-0-312-26977-7 | [http://www.shorel.com/faust.cfm "Little blue pills and a lot of gold..."] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120714110330/http://www.shorel.com/faust.cfm|date=2012-07-14}} | Culture & Lifestyle: [http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,786574,00.html "Sports Doping Statistics Reach Plateau in Germany"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5mq5SHQBa?url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,786574,00.html|date=20100117025039|dateformat=iso}} – ''[[Deutsche_Welle|Deutsche Welle]]'' – 26 February 2003 | [http://www.ishof.org/honorees/german_doping.htm "The East German Doping Machine"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080424085831/http://www.ishof.org/honorees/german_doping.htm|date=2008-04-24}} – International Swimming Hall of Fame | Culture & Lifestyle: [http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,1344595,00.html "East Germany's Doping Legacy Returns"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,1344595,00.html|date=20080308031046}} – ''[[Deutsche_Welle|Deutsche Welle]]'' – 10 January 2004 | Longman, Jere. – [http://www.nytimes.com/2004/01/26/sports/othersports/26STER.html?ei=5007&en=bc039fed4c6ea23a&ex=1390453200&partner=USERLAND&pagewanted=print&position= "East German Steroids' Toll: 'They Killed Heidi'"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/01/26/sports/othersports/26STER.html?ei=5007&en=bc039fed4c6ea23a&ex=1390453200&partner=USERLAND&pagewanted=print&position=|date=20151023062303}} – ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'' – 26 January 2004 | Harding, Luke. – [http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2005/nov/01/athletics.gdnsport3 "Forgotten victims of East German doping take their battle to court"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5n59qKs5A?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2005/nov/01/athletics.gdnsport3|date=20100127003743|dateformat=iso}} – ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]'' – 1 November 2005 | Jackson, Guy. Winning at Any Cost?: [http://portal.unesco.org/en/ev.php-URL_ID=33956&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html "Doping for glory in East Germany"] {{Wayback|url=http://portal.unesco.org/en/ev.php-URL_ID%3D33956%26URL_DO%3DDO_TOPIC%26URL_SECTION%3D201.html|date=20080611132033}} – [[UNESCO|UNESCO]] – September 2006 | [http://sports.espn.go.com/oly/news/story?id=2696038 "Ex-East German athletes compensated for doping"] {{Wayback|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/oly/news/story?id=2696038|date=20110512054102}} – [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] – (c/o [[ESPN|ESPN]]) – 13 December 2006 | [http://www.cbc.ca/sports/amateur/story/2006/12/13/geramny-doping.html "East German doping victims to get compensation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbc.ca/sports/amateur/story/2006/12/13/geramny-doping.html|date=20080602191752}} – [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] – (c/o [[Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation|CBC]] Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) – 13 December 2006 | Starcevic, Nesha. – [http://www.signonsandiego.com/sports/20061213-0605-germanydoping-compensation.html "East German doping victims to get compensation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.signonsandiego.com/sports/20061213-0605-germanydoping-compensation.html|date=20080603151007}} – [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] – (c/o ''[[San_Diego_Union-Tribune|San Diego Union-Tribune]]'') – 13 December 2006 | [http://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/2007-10-11-doping-damages_N.htm?csp=34 "Germany completes $4.1M payout to doping victims"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/2007-10-11-doping-damages_N.htm?csp=34|date=20080611132616}} – ''[[USA_Today|USA Today]]'' – 11 October 2007 | [http://www.thirteen.org/scienceandnature/east-germanys-secret-doping-program "East Germany’s Secret Doping Program"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090406073437/http://www.thirteen.org/scienceandnature/east-germanys-secret-doping-program|date=2009-04-06}} – ''[[Secrets_of_the_Dead|Secrets of the Dead]]'' – Thirteen/WNET – 7 May 2008</ref>

成功的另一个因素是对东德年轻人的系统培养。鼓励在校体育教师寻找6至10岁具有天赋的儿童。对年龄较大的学生安排就读重视体育（例如帆船，足球和游泳）的文法学校。这一政策也被用于在音乐或数学方面有才华的学生。

